                <h2 id="reporting">Reporting entities</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">PerformanceMetric entity</h3>
                <p>Defines performance metrics that can be tracked for products.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">ProductMetricValue entity</h3>
                <p>Stores submitted values for performance metrics.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">EnterpriseMetric entity</h3>
                <p>Defines and stores enterprise-level KPIs and metrics.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">FunctionalStandard entity</h3>
                <p>Stores DDaT functional standards information.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">FunctionalStandardAssessment entity</h3>
                <p>Records assessments of products against functional standards.</p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="administration">Administration entities</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">User entity</h3>
                <p>Stores user account information and preferences.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">UserPreference entity</h3>
                <p>Stores user-specific preferences and settings.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Objective entity</h3>
                <p>Stores strategic objectives that products and RAID items can align to.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Lookup tables</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>RiskTier:</strong> Risk tier definitions (product, programme, portfolio, enterprise)</li>
                    <li><strong>RiskType:</strong> Risk type categories (strategic, operational, financial, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>ActionSource:</strong> Sources where actions originate from</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="relationships">Entity relationships</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Junction tables (many-to-many relationships)</h3>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">RiskRiskType</h4>
                <p>Links risks to one or more risk types.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><code>RiskId</code> - Foreign key to Risk</li>
                    <li><code>RiskTypeId</code> - Foreign key to RiskType</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">RiskAction</h4>
                <p>Links risks to their mitigation actions.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><code>RiskId</code> - Foreign key to Risk</li>
                    <li><code>ActionId</code> - Foreign key to Action</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">IssueAction</h4>
                <p>Links issues to their resolution actions.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><code>IssueId</code> - Foreign key to Issue</li>
                    <li><code>ActionId</code> - Foreign key to Action</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">MilestoneRisk</h4>
                <p>Links milestones to associated risks.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><code>MilestoneId</code> - Foreign key to Milestone</li>
                    <li><code>RiskId</code> - Foreign key to Risk</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">MilestoneIssue</h4>
                <p>Links milestones to associated issues.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><code>MilestoneId</code> - Foreign key to Milestone</li>
                    <li><code>IssueId</code> - Foreign key to Issue</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">MilestoneAction</h4>
                <p>Links milestones to associated actions.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><code>MilestoneId</code> - Foreign key to Milestone</li>
                    <li><code>ActionId</code> - Foreign key to Action</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Key relationships</h3>
                
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <h4 class="h6">Product association</h4>
                    <p class="mb-0">Most RAID entities include a <code>FipsId</code> field that links to products in the FIPS CMS system. This is a string field containing the product's unique identifier.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <h4 class="h6">Strategic alignment</h4>
                    <p class="mb-0">Many entities include an optional <code>ObjectiveId</code> foreign key, allowing them to be linked to strategic objectives for alignment tracking.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <h4 class="h6">Soft delete pattern</h4>
                    <p class="mb-0">All RAID entities include an <code>IsDeleted</code> boolean flag. Records are not physically deleted but marked as deleted, preserving historical data and relationships.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <h4 class="h6">Audit trail</h4>
                    <p class="mb-0">All entities include <code>CreatedAt</code> and <code>UpdatedAt</code> DateTime fields for tracking when records were created and last modified.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2>Common patterns</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Entity naming conventions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Entities use Pascal case (e.g., <code>Risk</code>, <code>ActionSource</code>)</li>
                    <li>Properties use Pascal case (e.g., <code>Title</code>, <code>DueDate</code>)</li>
                    <li>Foreign keys include the entity name (e.g., <code>ObjectiveId</code>, <code>OwnerUserId</code>)</li>
                    <li>Navigation properties match the entity name (e.g., <code>Objective</code>, <code>OwnerUser</code>)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Status field conventions</h3>
                <p>Status fields use lowercase with underscores:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Risks: <code>new</code>, <code>open</code>, <code>treating</code>, <code>monitoring</code>, <code>closed</code></li>
                    <li>Issues: <code>open</code>, <code>in_progress</code>, <code>blocked</code>, <code>resolved</code>, <code>closed</code></li>
